    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "First of all, `isContract` checks the code size for _any_ address, not just the caller.\r\n\r\nWith that out of the way, there are multiple reasons why `tx.origin` is usually a bad idea, at least security-wise: see [here](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/683) an issue where removing it from Solidity was proposed, and [here](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/196/how-do-i-make-my-dapp-serenity-proof) a suggestion from Vitalik to 'not assume that `tx.origin` will continue to be usable or meaningful'.",
